    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>SMNTCS Free Gift for WooCommerce is a lightweight plugin to give away free gifts to your WooCommerce customers.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload the plugin to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory.</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the <code>Plugins</code> menu in WordPress.</li>\n<li>Go to <code>Appearance</code> » <code>Customize</code>.</li>\n<li>Enable free gifts.</li>\n<li>Adjust settings based on your needs.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<dt id='how%20do%20i%20enable%20free%20gifts%3F'>\nHow do I enable free gifts?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to <code>Products</code> » <code>Categories</code> and create a category for the gifts, e.g. Gift.</li>\n<li>Go to <code>Products</code> » <code>Add Product</code> and create your gift product.</li>\n<li>Make sure to set the <code>Regular price</code> to 0 and the <code>Catalog visibility</code> to <code>Hidden</code>.</li>\n<li>Go to <code>Appearance</code> » <code>Customise</code> » <code>Customise</code>.</li>\n<li>Activate the checkbox <code>Enable free gift</code>.</li>\n<li>Provide the <code>Minimum cart value</code>, e.g. 10.00.</li>\n<li>Select the <code>Gift category</code>.</li>\n<li>Provide a message for <code>Message \"Proceed shopping\"</code>.</li>\n<li>Provide a message for <code>Button \"Proceed shopping\"</code>.</li>\n<li>Provide a message for <code>Message \"Add gift\"</code>.</li>\n<li>Provide a message for <code>Button \"Add gift\"</code>.</li>\n<li>Click on <code>Save &amp; Publish</code>.</li>\n</ol>\n</p>\n<dt id='can%20i%20create%20multiple%20gifts%3F'>\nCan I create multiple gifts?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes, you can create multiple gifts.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id='i%20have%20multiple%20gifts%20set%20up.%20can%20my%20customers%20choose%20their%20gift%3F'>\nI have multiple gifts set up. Can my customers choose their gift?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>No, at the moment a random gift will be assigned.</p>\n</p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.8 (2023.10.15)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Test up to WP 6.4</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.7 (2022.12.03)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Test up to WP 6.1</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.6 (2020.04.14)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nielslange/smntcs-woocommerce-free-gift/issues/14\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Add check if WooCommerce is installed</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nielslange/smntcs-woocommerce-free-gift/issues/12\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Move settings into WooCommerce customizer</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.5 (2020.04.07)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nielslange/smntcs-woocommerce-free-gift/issues/9\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Declaring required and supported WooCommerce version</a></li>\n<li>Test up to WP 5.4</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.4 (2019.11.18)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Test up to WP 5.3</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.3 (2019.06.28)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Test up to WP 5.2</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2 (2019.02.19)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Add README.md</li>\n<li>Test up to WP 5.0</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1 (2016.07.22)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Save settings as option, not as theme_mod</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0 (2016.07.20)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
